reviews.review_text: Trust To the taper Tony. I seem to download many of your shows. I like your feel for for each arena/venue.  This was an odd night for me,went to eat before the show and took my time.Not sure why but had been getting burnt by the end of this tour. Started sunny down south ended with snow flurrys here in upstate. Nothing like the good old grateful dead to keep us going from day to day. I got back to the show in time to try getting in during Aiko. Someone had givin me a ticket that turned out to be fake. That sucked. Now it was up to me and the friends inside to get me in. Turns out they had many fakes this night. i went to one of gates told my story of sadness to some guy who could care less. just then i was handed a real ticket. seems things always worked out.  I had got in just in time for Brown eyed.  again your shows smoke Tony.  thanks

Peak Experience  Rated a 5 for the best memories ...  brought a halloween mask into the show.  A REALLY scary mask.  I forgot I had it with me until I was searched at the door.  Then after getting on the floor and dancing a few songs I put it on.  My one friend still talks about it!  In retrospect it was WAY TO SCARY to do to anyone considering the state of mind.  
Next memory is one in a billion.  While at the very back and tip top of the stadium I realized I could climb up!  I climbed into the rafters and proceeded to make my way through the rafters all the way up to the band.  I then pulled myself on my stomach until I could have spit on Jerry!  I was directly above him!  After a short stint I crawled back and attempted to get my buddy to come up with me.  He would have nothing to do with it.  I was covered in dirt and soot.  Looking at it now, I was lucky to not have dropped anything on the old man!  Lucky kid!  25 years ago today!
